OL,3,CBenefits system 'not sustainable',
OL,4,Csenior Labour MP claims
OL,6,FLiberal Democrat MP James MacClearley
OL,7,Fsaid: "When you look at Pip, you're
OL,8,Flooking at some of the most vulnerable
OL,9,Fpeople in society.
OL,11,F"There's real fear out there. People
OL,12,Fare frightened. They thought this
OL,13,Fgovernment was elected to stand up for
OL,14,Fthem and instead they seem to be
OL,15,Fpicking on them."
OL,17,FMPs are expected to vote on the
OL,18,FUniversal Credit and Personal
OL,19,FIndependence Payment Bill on 1 July,
OL,20,Fwhen it receives its second reading in
OL,21,Fthe House of Commons.
